animal.description: Hey there! Named after Mr. Ferrari himself, Enzo is running at the speed of the fastest car and that speed is FAST. This dude loves everything about life! His first few years of life were spent on a chain but that is over and he is ready to LOVE life. His favorite activities are playing ball, squeaky toys and getting cuddles. He likes to make us laugh with his silly antics and would NEVER turn down a snack. He is learning how to have manners. This boy has no idea he is 60lbs and is positive he is a lap dog! He is a smart boy who knows how to sit, stay, drop it and down! We are working on fine tuning his stay and learning leave it and off. He is a rough and tumble kind of guy so we recommend sturdier children and no feline friends. Mr. Enzo is heartworm Postive. He has been started on treatment and has a treatment plan! Please send us an email at wchsadopt@gmail.com for more information or visit our website wchumane.org to fill out an adoption application! Due to Covid, we are asking all adoption paperwork filled out and submitted prior to adoption and we are appointment only.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

AdoptaGSD.org

Please consider that some of these dogs have been abandoned or ignored by their previous owners, having little interaction with someone who cares about them.

When adopted, they will need time to adjust to the changes in their life.

Hi, my name is RoxyAnn, and I'm a beautiful three year old GSD who was transferred from a shelter where I was surrendered by my former owner when the landlord changed the policy where I lived for three years to no longer allow pets. My former owner described me as sweet, playful, dominant and protective. She said I'm comfortable with both men and women. Since coming to rescue, the volunteers have introduced me to other dogs in a controlled setting to see how I do, and I'm doing well. I can sometimes play roughly with other dogs, so it's important for my play sessions to be supervised. I seem to be insecure and would definitely benefit from living with an adopter who won't baby me or feel sorry for me, but rather help build my confidence. More info to come. If you are interested, please go to adoptagsd.org and submit an online application. My adoption fee is $350.

Although we do our best to keep our adoptable animals page as current as possible,the animals you see may already be in an adoption process.

animal.description:
This sweet girl's name is Annie, and with a face like this we know her fur-ever home is only a day away!

Annie is an eight year old Bloodhound that is looking for a second chance at love. Annie loves her humans, is great with children and even gets along with other canines. Being a Bloodhound, it is not surprising that she follows her nose, and that can lead her to getting into trouble. Annie needs proper exercise and mental stimulation, or she will get bored and find a way to entertain herself.
An active owner with breed experience, the willingness to help her with her leash skills and a home where she will get lots of exercise and love is where she will do best. 

Annie is all up to date on shots, microchipped and is spayed. 

Will you be Annie's happily ever after?

If you are interested in adopting Annie, all you have to do is submit an adoption application, which can be found on our website at www.hoodriveradoptadog.org. 

Applications are reviewed and approved in the order in which they are received.
Once your submitted application has been approved,  my adoption counselor will be in contact to discuss the next steps, answer any questions and to schedule a meet and greet.

Meet and greets are only scheduled after an application has been approved. COVID-19 safety protocols are in place, and a mask must be worn at the meet and greet - no exceptions.

My adoption fee is $200

animal.description:
IN VERMONT

Meet Prince! Here is his video collage in NC:

https://youtu.be/5l9GjUprZD8

Prince is 3 years old (approx. DOB 11-3-17), male, 50 lbs., vetted, is or will be neutered, and micro-chipped. Prince was dropped off to the shelter by his family positive for Heartworms (has since been treated). He was incredibly scared and very submissive in the shelter; shaking and trembling. In his new world in Foster Prince is untrusting of strangers. We have no idea why this boy doesn't trust but he is very loyal and loving to his people. He is currently working on building his confidence and learning how to be appropriately socialized. Prince is quiet and laid back; and is doing well with his 4 legged foster sibling! Stay tuned for more information as Prince is a new rescue!

If you are interested in adopting Prince please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out his Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

animal.description: Prince is a sweet, senior boy who came to PACC due to no fault of his own after spending 11 years with the same owner. He's house trained and since coming to PACC, has been a very good boy. In play group, he was friendly and appropriate with other dogs and staffers say he was an easy going guy who mostly did his own thing. He has been very friendly with staffers and volunteers, but is a bit more selective when it comes to dogs, so we recommend a meet-and-greet with any resident dogs. And while he loves adults, he can be a bit of a grump when it comes to kids, so we recommend Prince go to a home free from small children (there are still some of those out there, right?) Prince is a loving, senior pup who would love to spend the remainder of his golden years in a home, rather than the shelter. If you've got some room on your couch and in your heart for this sweet old gentleman, make an appointment to meet him today.

animal.description:
Snickers turns 15 years young in January 2021. She is a beautiful dachshund terrier mix. This relaxed girl is looking for a quiet home where she can live out her golden years. She would be ok with a calm dog companion (preferably another senior) but would not do well with high energy or dominant dogs. She could also be placed with a dog-friendly cat.

This poor girl was not in good shape when she arrived- She had worms, hair loss and was peeing very frequently and uncomfortable. She has some arthritis in her back legs, but has begun taking supplements and gets around just fine.

She has had her blood work back and it's looking fairly normal, which is great given her age. She is being treated for a Cushing's and has a dental scheduled at the end of January. We expect her to be ready for adoption at the very end of January once the vet has rechecked her teeth.

Could Snicker's be the perfect addition to your family? Please apply on our website to be considered:

https://www.portlanddachshundrescue.org/adoptionform

animal.description:
Breed: Terrier mix
Sex: Neutered Male
DOB: ~09/20/2018
Weight: 22 lbs
Energy Level: Medium-High
Personality Type: Energetic, Affectionate, Playful
History: Transferred from another shelter
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ years
Fence Requirements: Preferred, not required
Ideal Home: Active home! Apartments may be ok with very active adopters.
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
BULLY MIX- Grey and white – sleek coat.  About 48lbs
ADULT FEMALE;  Est DOB: 10/2014
ARRIVAL: December 19, 2020
HISTORY:  Celeste arrived as a stray at a high kill shelter.  When space became an issue, we spoke up for her.

Everyone LOVES Celeste!  I mean loves!  This middle age sweetheart is loving and doting and just as easy going as they come.  Never meeting a stranger,  Celeste is extremely gentle in her ways, very even keel and accepting of all.  A slow and steady off leash roamer in our fenced in areas,  she is really open to meeting/interacting with anyone who might cross her path, either human or canine.   At the top of her “Things I enjoy most,”  would be all over body rubs and simply chilling by her human.  Celeste also has a casual interest to run and play with balls.  She has an old soul feel about her and is not overly clingy.  She does not ask for much but gives back so very much.  Celeste is graced with a disposition which is perfectly suited for folks of most ages from younger kids to retired folks.   A very peaceful, delightful older lady!

animal.description:
Hi hoomans 

I am Mako and I am about 1.5 years old and Border Collie X.  

I would love a home where my hooman family members are home a lot of the time.  And I so want another young active canine Brother or Sister to play with.  

I love playing with my friends at doggie daycamp and going on hikes.  I have also been going to some training classes to learn about who's my pack leader.  

Do you have an active lifestyle and want to add a way cute guy like me? 

Call and see if we might fit.  Please fill out and application too!  Thanks a lot for reading a bit about me! 

Love, Mako

Mako is up to date on his vaccinations, neutered and is currently being fostered in Flagstaff. His adoption fee is $150

We are a small rescue/foster group without an animal shelter. If you are interested in meeting Mako, please fill out an online adoption application, located here: https://tubacityhumanesociety.org/tuba-city-humane-society-dogcat-online-adoption-application/ 
You can find more  information about our adoption process here:
https://tubacityhumanesociety.org/adoptions/

Once we receive your application, which answers basic questions for us, we will have a conversation with you, before setting up a meeting. For more information, please contact Deb at dfranklin@tubacityhumanesociety.org or by phone at (928) 853-1046 (No calls after 7 p.m. please.)

If interested in adopting a pet from our shelter you will need to fill out a request to adopt. There will be a overnight wait to get this approved. If approved, there is a $20 adoption fee for cats, and kittens. Adult dogs adoption fee is $75.00. Adoption fees for adult dogs at the shelter more than 2 weeks reduces to $25. Adoption fee for puppies or purebred dogs (no papers) is $100.  If not spayed or neutered, a deposit is required. The deposit is $130 for dogs and $55 for cats. Your deposit is returned after the animal is spayed/neutered. All animals adopted from the shelter MUST be spayed/neutered. Dogs arriving at the shelter receive DA2PP and Bordetella. Cats receive a vaccine for Rhinotracheitis-Calici-Panleukopenia-Chlamydia Psittaci. The animals at our shelter have been picked up stray. Please remember this when requesting additional information about the animals. Questions can be emailed to emporiakansasanimalshelter@gmail.com

More info coming soon! 

Call/text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387. 

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING THIS PET? Fill out an Adoption Application now! Appointments can also be made to meet a pet by calling us at 913-671-PETS (913-671-7387).  

ADOPTION INFORMATION:
Prior to adoption, our animals are: 
**Tested for diseases 
**Vaccinated 
**Spayed/neutered 
**Microchipped 

NO COST adoptions with an encouraged donation are accepted. 

The Pet Connection also offers adopters a FREE veterinary examination and a medical care support plan for 60 days after adoption, as well as lifetime behavioral training, safe sanctuary for pets returned in emergency situations, extensive assistance with lost and found pets, and other expert pet services in a variety of areas, including pet selection, behavioral issues, general training, nutrition, and transition to adoptive homes.

Please visit our website at www.thepetconnection.org for more information about The Pet Connection and for a full listing of our available pets, 

Call or text The Pet Connection at 913-671-7387 if you can foster, adopt, or sponsor a special needs dog or cat! 

The Pet Connection is a membership organization operating a no-kill adoption center in Shawnee, Kansas.

Sweet Grace Needs Our Help!!

2020 isn't over yet and the dogs need us! We were able to get Grace off the streets of Mexico and to our vet ASAP! Sadly, x-rays confirmed damage to her rear leg that has been this way for some time. Grace will need amputation surgery to relieve her of pain and a limb that is now badly deformed. Grace is a doll, she is young and has already adapted to being a tri-pod. We are grateful we were able to get her off the streets before anything else happened to her. If you would like to make a year end donation to help with Gracie's medical care here are ways to help:

animal.description:
Carolina Boxer Rescue is a volunteer run, 501(c)3 non-profit organization. Our mission: To balance the health, safety, and welfare needs of Boxers in the Carolinas (and parts of Virginia and Georgia) by providing a loving and safe environment for stray, abused, impounded and owner surrendered dogs by placing them in foster homes and ultimately - forever homes.

________________________________________________________________________________________

Dog's Name: Birch

Dog's Approximate Age: 6 years

Gender: Male

Dog's Size: Pocket Boxer (under 50lbs as adult and healthy weight)

Dog's Weight: 44 pounds 2 weeks ago but gaining steadily.

Good with small dogs?: Don't know yet

Good with big dogs?: Don't know yet

Good with cats?: Don't know yet

Good with kids?: Don't know yet

Any medical issues?: We are starting heartworm treatment Dec 2nd.

Crate trained?: Yes

House trained?: Yes

Heartworms?: Yes

12/1/20:
Well, first, I am named after a tree, cool, right? I am white, like the paper birch but have beautiful black dots in my skin that show through, so, I literally look like a birch tree!!! I still have some fur that is growing back in, but, man, wow has my fur been growing in since I've had an awesome bath and lots of good food, water and exercise! I'm leaning towards being a rock star! All the women in my neighborhood just swoon over me on my walks!

Speaking of rockstars, I know they are all about sound, but..... I'm not, i can't really hear but don't worry, because i am an awesome boxer! Guess what? My first sense is smell! and my second, is sight! Hearing is just my 3rd sense and not that important to me. I like to make eye contact and see what my MF is signaling with her hands so I know what to do. And, I am soooo thankful I do not have to listen to the human boys' drum sessions!

Oh, did I mention, I LOVE to walk! I do an awesome job on walks! I sometimes like to step off the trail to smell new and different things, I am a dog, what do you expect??? But, I am always happy to respond to your slight tugs on the leash that tell me to "come on", or "go left", or "go right". I am so smart!

I am not sure how I will feel during the heart worm treatment but know I will be loved during the process!

Cheers my friends and I will keep you updated!

_____________________________________________________________________________

Come visit carolinaboxerrescue.org to learn more about me and see more pictures. Learn about our adoption process too!

animal.description:
Meet Dupree! A very sweet and slightly shy nine-year-old Terrier mix weighing about 9 lbs. This little girl will steal your heart and she is finally ready to find her forever home! Dupree was turned into the shelter by a Good Samaritan with a very, very nasty leg wound. It was bad enough that they felt they needed to amputate and they put out a plea to the rescue community to save her. I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue stepped up and she was immediately taken to the vet for medical care. Since she had no broken bones it was decided to see if she could heal on her own with attentive loving care in a foster home. It was a long month with many vet visits and bandage changes, but she is all healed up completely and you can't even tell any different! She is ready to find her forever family! Her ideal home will have a calm environment and she would love to be the only princess around so she can get all the love and attention! Cats are fine but she doesn't really like other dogs bothering her. Do you want to give Dupree the second chance she truly deserves? Get your application in today, we promise you won't be disappointed!

If you are interested in adopting, please visit the I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue website and complete an adoption application: www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter shots up to date micro-chip fecal and vet check

Meet Southern Belle Ellie!

She was nothing but skin and bones when she was rescued. After two surgeries to remove mammary tumors, heartworm treatment, and lots of TLC with her foster mom, Ellie got a clean bill of health from the vet! She is ready to find her furever!

Ellie's foster mom says she is basically the perfect dog! She even goes with her to the quiet office where she works most days! Ellie has the biggest and most beautiful smile and loves people. She is wonderful on leash, loves walks, and gets compliments whenever she is out walking with her foster mom. Ellie loves car rides, is totally housebroken, and does well in and out of her crate. She is a BIG cuddler, loves affection, and is always ready to shower her people with kisses 

Ellie would do best in a calm and relaxed home, preferably with a family who will treat her like a queen all day! She does get along with calm dogs and is friendly when she meets them on walks. Playful, hyper dogs are not for her. As always, a meet and greet with resident or frequently visiting dogs will be required.
Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
DESMUND is a tall, leggy, handsome, plott hound and maybe Great Dane (?!) mix puppy who is estimated around 7 months old. He’s already around 60 lbs and so will be a good sized adult, and is fully vetted, microchipped and neutered. He does take a little bit to open up (he spent 10 mins terrified to come out of the crate at his foster's initially - but then after that, he relaxes and is fine) but then once he's comfortable, he is very chill. He does enjoy walks but seems to prefer to just chill on the couch and relax, chewing on his bones and toys. He does still have a lot of that puppy chew energy, so he needs to be kept busy with toys and appropriate things to mouth - he is just a giant puppy and would benefit from some training classes and maybe another relaxed older dog to show him the doggy ropes). He's housetrained and crate trained and working on basic commands. He should be fine around kids, but would be best not around really young ones or ones who aren't able to give him space as he acclimates to his forever home. His foster reports he is just a big goofball who has no idea of his size. He's not yet cat-tested. Contact us for more details as we continue to get more information from our foster.

Adoption fee covers: all vetting to age (including deworming, deflea etc ), spay/neuter (to be done at 6-8 months of age if not already done and included in adoption fee,  free 30 days of pet insurance, 6 week obedience course (or reimbursement for positive-based classes), and lifetime support of rescue.

Please fill out an application here for consideration: Tinyurl.Com/appshdr

* During this COVID-19 crisis, we are essentially doing only virtual application processing and meetings are using social distancing practices. We will not have any open hours until further notice and doing meet and greets by appointment with the utmost caution for personal safety. We are not a shelter so there are NO DOGS AT THE SHOP unless we have open hours. All our dogs are in foster care and are available to be seen by appointment.

NOTE: If a dog is listed as Adoptable, he or she is still available at that time. Also, our adoption area is within a several hour radius of us in Rochester, NY (NOT including Canada - sorry!)

animal.description:
"Hi there, I'm Mutt Damon! I am about 4 years old and weigh around 40 pounds. Can you believe a dog as cute as me is homeless? Well, I just joined the adoptable doggy crew at Providence Animal Center after being scooped up from ACCT Philly and am waiting for a wonderful person or family to adopt me! I'm all set to move into my 'furever' home - already neutered, microchipped & up to date on vaccinations.

The staff think that I would fit right into a quieter home with an active family & children aged 5 or older - as long as there is a quiet space so I can have some 'me time'. They also think I'd love a doggy roommate to be pals with - but cats, not so much, can't quite figure them out.

I was able to spend some time with a wonderful foster and they have the following to say about me:

"Mutt Damon is very friendly and loves meeting other dogs. He plays great with my dogs -- both big and small. He's an excellent co-pilot and enjoys tagging along for errands. He has good leash manners. He's food motivated, so I think he would be a great training partner! When meeting new people, he is a bit shy, so I think he is often misunderstood. The trick is to give him treats when first meeting him! He will warm up quickly. He loves having his belly rubbed and enjoys cuddling. He will cuddle with dogs and then come over to cuddle with me. He is the sweetest dog. He quickly became my best friend and I loved having him. His new family will be extremely lucky!" 

I am lucky enough to be staying with one of PAC's fabulous foster partners, Perfect Pooch in King of Prussia, while I wait for my forever family to find me.  If you are interested in more information about me including my most up-to-date status and/or would like to set up a meeting with me, please contact the fabulous staff at Perfect Pooch today at 610-337-7698! We hope to hear from you soon!  XOXO, Mutt Damon

P.S. Someone is so excited for me to find my fur-ever home, that they have sponsored my adoption fee! That means I can join your family today for FREE! Woohoo!!"


-------
During your appointment, you will be able to meet a selection of pets in the Kennels or Cattery that day. New pets are arriving daily!
-------

Providence Animal Center relies on adoption fees and donations to save pets! Adoption fees vary per pet. To find out this pet’s adoption fee or for more information, please call the Adoption Center with this pet’s ID number.

Can’t adopt? Consider fostering or donating! Visit https://providenceac.org/support-us/ for more information on how you can support the lifesaving mission!

animal.description:
Topher (short for Tofurky) & gal-pal YamYam were surrendered to an overcrowded county shelter right around Thanksgiving. Having spent the better part of their young chiweenie lives being used/abused as a breeding pair, they are now happily retired from that business and in search of a home to start over as dogs of leisure. 

Topher is around six years old (just a kid in little dog years!) and tops out around 13 magnificent pounds. For our volunteers, it was love at first sight ... those expressive ears, that ever-wagging tail, and his perky little personality. He was in dire need of dental work when he arrived at our shelter but, 12 less teeth later, he is a much happier boy. And will do anything for a snack :O)

We believe Topher was treated poorly in his previous life. He cowers when you reach for him, and doesn't like hands over his head or having his harness put on. While he is initially guarded around strangers, it only takes a little patience and a proffered lap for him to reveal his sweet, snugly side. After years of being conditioned to expect rough treatment, he is learning to accept kindness from humans.
 
Topher is crate trained and good on leash. He will benefit from continued confidence-building and socialization. Topher and Yam-Yam can be adopted as a pair, but would be equally fine going their separate ways. Each would be perfectly happy being your one-and-only furbaby, or might possibly be willing to consider sharing your love and attention with another dog. As is often the case with chihuahuas and especially factoring in his background/trust issues, Topher requests the his inner circle be limited to adults and older kids who can understand and respect his limits and sensitivities. Please visit www.STAF.org for more information about our adoption process.

•  All of our animals are spayed/neutered and current on shots.
•  We do not do same-day adoptions; we ask that you return for a follow-up visit before taking an animal home.
•  You must be 21 years or older to adopt from STAF.
•  We require a 4-foot-tall physical fence for homes with children under the age of 11. We also may require a physical fence for specific dogs on a case-by-case basis, depending on each dog’s behavior and exercise needs.
•  Due in part to increasing coyote activity/incidents in the area and the difficulty of predicting how a dog will respond to invisible fence training, we can not adopt to homes with invisible fences.
•  We do request vet and personal references.
•  We can facilitate adoptions within a 75-mile radius of our Cincinnati-based shelter.

animal.description:
We are currently closed to the public and will only be responding to pet inquiries accompanying an online adoption application. Once animals are posted, we immediately begin receiving applications. With one volunteer available to review all applications, we appreciate your patience as you wait for an email response. Adoption appointments are scheduled in the order that approved applications are received. You can find our adoption procedures and online application at warmhearts.org/adopt.

Opal transferred in from another shelter, so we don't have any background information. She came to us with substantial hair loss but look at her now! She is ready to move into her forever home and receive lots of TLC. Opal is very affectionate and loves attention from her human friends, but she does not seem to share that love with other dogs. Opal's estimated DOB is 11/22/2018. She weighs about 62 pounds and is most likely done growing. We cannot be sure that Opal is house trained.

HSPC's adoption fee is seventy-five-dollars through December 31, 2020, unless stated otherwise within the pet's description. At times, our adoption fees are lowered during special events that are posted to our website or Facebook page. Every pet that is available for adoption has been spayed/neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccinations including heartworm preventative (canines). Adopters are required to schedule a wellness exam with their veterinarian at their cost within 7 days of adoption.

Please only submit one application. Once you are contacted by email, you will have an opportunity to provide us with any additional animal(s) under consideration.

animal.description:
Carolina Boxer Rescue is a volunteer run, 501(c)3 non-profit organization. Our mission: To balance the health, safety, and welfare needs of Boxers in the Carolinas (and parts of Virginia and Georgia) by providing a loving and safe environment for stray, abused, impounded and owner surrendered dogs by placing them in foster homes and ultimately - forever homes.

________________________________________________________________________________________

Dog's Name: Harper

Dog's Approximate Age: 8 years

Gender: Female

Dog's Size: Medium (50lbs to 70lbs. as adult and healthy weight)

Dog's Weight: 54 pounds

Good with small dogs?: Yes

Good with big dogs?: Yes

Good with cats?: Don't know yet

Good with kids?: Yes, all ages

Any medical issues?: Not sure just yet. Taking her to the vet on 12/15/2020 for a check up.

Crate trained?: Don't know yet

House trained?: Yes

Heartworms?: No

12/17/20:
Hi! My name is Harper and I was picked up as a stray in South Carolina. Living on the streets without a family was tough. My skin & hair suffered from not having the proper nourishment. Now that I am in a loving foster home, I know my skin & hair are going to improve soon. Upon arrival to my foster home, I checked out every room and the yard. There are so many new sights and smells here! I really like other dogs, so I quickly made friends with my foster mom's 8 year old boxer named Castle. My foster home also has a three year old child and I like him too. I am a pretty calm girl so I know my manners when it comes to kids. I settled in and adjusted to my new foster home really quickly. I love breakfast and dinner time and I really love getting treats! My foster mom was delighted that I knew how to sit, and she was really surprised that I knew how to shake paw. My foster mom takes me on daily walks with Castle. I'm pretty good on the leash and easy to handle. After our walk, I love to take a nice long nap on one of the many doggie beds here. I like to be in the kitchen to watch my foster mom cook dinner, but she created a barricade to keep me out because she said the kitchen is too small. I still watch her from the dining room beyond her barricade. Ha! Ha! I am affectionate, I like to give hugs, and I like to follow my foster mom around to see what she is doing. I really am enjoying being in a home and getting taken care of.

_____________________________________________________________________________

Come visit carolinaboxerrescue.org to learn more about me and see more pictures. Learn about our adoption process too!

_____________________________________________________________________________

Meet Trix, a sweet and reserved shepherd mix estimated to be a year old and weighing an estimated 38 pounds. Trix has a back leg issue that we initially thought needed surgery. As it turns out, it is a birth defect and our vet doesn't think it bothers her to have corrective surgery at this time. With that said, she may need corrective surgery or pain management in the future so any family should be prepared to handle any issues that might arise in her senior years. It wouldn't be fair to adopt her, keep her through her youth and return her when she needs medical care. 

Trix came in through an animal control so there's not much background info but any family willing to commit to her forever, potential medical needs and all, apply today. Potty training and crate training unknown.

animal.description:
Benny is a handsome Pyr boy looking for his Pyrfect furever home! Benny is housetrained and does fairly well on a leash. He knows most basic commands, and in typical Pyr fashion, he listens to them when he feels like it :) There’s two things Benny loves...his humans and his food! He’s not crazy about the idea of sharing either of them. Benny has gotten along with other dogs in the past, except for when food or human attention is involved. Benny is looking for a patient family, that understands him and will put him in a position to succeed in these situations. Benny is a typical Pyr in that his main purpose for being on this earth is to protect. He is on high alert for any incoming threats. Benny loves belly rubs and cuddles. He was shaved due to matting but his gorgeous coat will grow back again soon. He loves playing fetch in his yard, even if he isn’t the most graceful. Despite his clumsiness, Benny will impress you with his unfailing ability to catch a flying piece of food in his mouth! Benny desires love more than anything else in life and he promises to not let you down. He’s looking for the same commitment from his new humans. If you are the family that can commit to helping Benny live up to his full pawtential, apply for this sweet, loving, goofy boy today!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Intake Type: (7/11) Owner Surrender 

Medical Observation:
(7/11) PE: NSF, BAR

Behavior Observation:
(7/12) Volunteer Eval - Easy to leash/social. Presented at front of kennel with four on floor. Easy to return to kennel. Moderate pulling on leash when first walking, but pulling decreased on the way back (very hot outside). Solicits pets nicely, interested and sociable with handler in the run. She was a little nervous of surroundings and stayed close to handler. Gentle and friendly. No interest in play. Interested in squeaky toy but does not take possession. Takes cheese gently from hand. Evaled gold. Knows sit.
(7/12) Per Lifesaving -- Loose and social in kennel. Easily leashed. Walks well through building. Pulls moderately on leash outside. Calm in run and ignores handler, but does allow handler to approach and allows all over handling. After a little bit of time does begin to engage with handler on her own. Engages in tag by running behind handler, does not get jumpy or mouthy at all and disengages when handler stops running. No issues returning to kennel or removing leash. 
(7/11) Per Vet Staff -- friendly
(7/11) Per Previous Owners -- Loving and great with people and children. Playful with dogs her size. Tried to crate but she would escape. Great with people, no signs of aggression towards people. Know sit and stay and lay. Severe aggression to small animals, has killed multiple small animals. Not good with cats or small dogs. 


This animal is currently available from foster care through ACCT Philly's Adoptions Programs. This animal is not onsite. If the foster has not listed a personal email, contact foster@acctphilly.org to be put in touch with the foster. 

We encourage you to visit our shelter during our adoption hours to view our complete selection of available animals. In preparation for your visit, please make sure to visit http://www.acctphilly.org/adopt/ to review our adoption requirements, hours of operation, upcoming events, and more! 

Is this your missing pet? If you believe so, please make sure to follow the instructions listed at http://www.acctphilly.org/lostpet/ so that we can make sure that you are reunited as soon as possible!

animal.description:
Ace is a black Labrador Retriever mix who weighs about 60lbs. He is sweet, goofy guy. He lived on a chain prior to coming into rescue without any veterinary care, but he is current now. We were initially told that he was 10 years old, but he is very active, has very good teeth so we think he is younger and maybe 5-6 years old. Ace had done a great job learning manners and house training. He is learning also basic commands like sit. He loves to be with people and to please his people.

Ace is an active dog and would like a home that will play with him or take him for walks and on new adventures. At this time we are recommending a home with no other dogs so that Ace can shower his love on his humans!

If you are interested in adopting Ace please submit an inquiry directly with Greater Charlotte SPCA by visiting charlottespca.org/adopt. ***Because our rescue is composed entirely of volunteers and we require a home check for each of our adoptable pets prior to them going to their new homes, local applications will take precedence. We will accept out of town applications, but any family further than 60 miles from Charlotte is responsible for finding a representative of a rescue local to them that is willing to perform the home check. All out of town applicants will also have to be willing to drive to Charlotte to meet/pick up the pet as soon as the application is approved.***

animal.description:
Cinder is a young (under 2) male lab/pitbull mix that is amazingly sweet and playful. He was taken in as a stray by a family that cared for him, but their house burnt down and they could not take him to their new home. He was left to live in a chicken coop where he was fed 3 times a week. No local rescue would take him because he was a pitbull and at the time had two very large masses on his legs.

Rico Pet Recovery took him in. He has been vaccinated and neutered and the masses have been removed from his legs. The vet says there is a small chance the masses will come back (<25%)
He is very playful, loves his belly rubbed, loves toys and is getting better every day on the leash. He does not have accidents in his kennel, but has not been in our house. He is good with other dogs and kids, but likes to chase cats.
Apply for Cinder at ricopetrecovery.org

Our mission: To balance the health, safety, and welfare needs of Boxers in the Carolinas (and parts of Virginia and Georgia) by providing a loving and safe environment for stray, abused, impounded and owner surrendered dogs by placing them in foster homes and ultimately - forever homes.

Dog's Name: Dante

Dog's Approximate Age: 2-3 years

Gender: Male

Dog's Size: Medium (50lbs to 70lbs. as adult and healthy weight)

Dog's Weight: 55 pounds

Good with small dogs?: Don't know yet

Good with big dogs?: Yes

Good with cats?: Yes

Good with kids?: Don't know yet

Any medical issues?: No

Crate trained?: Yes

House trained?: Working on it

Heartworms?: No

12/30/20:
Hi! I'm a sweet boy who loves to cuddle. I'm very good in my crate and I don't rip up my bed. I'm just starting to enjoy toys and I chase after a tennis ball great! I've only been in my foster home a week so I'm still adjusting but so far I've only had tinkle accidents when I get really excited. I'm not too big and not too small. I am tall enough to steal food off the counter though and we are learning not to do that. Hey, everyone else gets a sparkly cookie, why not me right? My foster parents were told I'm good with dogs and cats, and they have both. We are meeting each other slowly, but so far I'm happy to meet them. I love my big soft blanket and I'm very good on a leash. Will update more when my foster parents get to know me better. Did I mention I have a cute pout? I sure do and I know how to use it! Haha.

animal.description:
Avocado is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Avocado is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~7 years
Weight: ~52lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Has done well with free roam while his foster's have been away for brief periods of time. 
Dog sociability: Selective with his dog friends. May be a match for some, but not all. Does best with slow introductions over time with calm dogs that do not get into his space.
Cat sociability: No cats, please!
Kids: Unknown, but resources guards food/bones occasionally so older kids/teenagers only
Ideal home: Avocado would prefer to not live in a high-rise/elevator building but is pretty adaptable to most other living environments! 

Don't let his Resting Grumpy Face fool you - Avocado is a happy, fun-loving guy! He does kiss on the first date but does so like a gentleman. His wiggle-factor is off the charts and he's the first in line for a cuddle session. The way he bounces down the stairs will actually make you want to go outside during Chicago winters. Avocado loves a good marrow bone or lickimat smeared with some peanut butter. He's done great with the other dog in his home and overall is such an easygoing guy. This boy is ready for his forever home!

Avocado's adoption fee is 150. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. Avocado will be due for a dental cleaning and extraction of a fractured tooth after adoption which will be the adopter's responsibility.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

She’s spayed, heartworm negative, up to date, and on preventatives.

Crate trained and working on potty training.  
This sweetheart is ready for a forever home!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

Louie's stats:
Age: 2 years
Weight: 55 pounds
Good with kids: Older kids only.
Good with dogs: Yes
Good with cats: Unsure
Fenced yard: Required.
Suitable for townhouse and/or apartment: No
House trained: Yes.
Crate trained: Yes.
Barks when left alone: No.
Chews inappropriate items: No
Training: knows Sit, Come, No, Stop
Activity level: I am quite active, but I also like to sit with you
I need an experienced adopter.

Louie writes:
I’m ready for anything – a romp at the dog park, a game of fetch or a good cuddle!

I enjoy chasing balls and toys and will bring them back if you throw them, although I might not drop them right away. I love playing tug, too. (I usually win because I’m very strong.) I have a thing about rocks and branches – they just appeal to me and I like to carry them around. I also like to jump and I’m very good at it! Just watch my video!

I love getting attention from my people. I will curl up next to them or on them, if they let me. (I’m not that heavy!) I like being hugged. I’m good at letting my people know when I have to go outside.

I’m working on my outside manners, like walking nicely on leash. There’s just so much interesting stuff out there! I love going for car rides, and sticking my head out the window. I sometimes have a hard time controlling my enthusiasm, so my foster mom is teaching me the Wait command. And I know it’s hard to believe, but I’m a little nervous meeting new people. But after a little while, I’m asking them for pets and belly rubs.

I have a lot of energy, so need a family that will spend time playing with me and helping me be the best dog ever!

animal.description:
Meet LUCY!
-Female
-Approximately 3 years old
-Stafford MIX

Lucy is:
-Playful
-Loving
-Friendly
-Sweet/Kind
-Curious
-Smart
-NOT good with cats
-Not good with dogs at the moment, HAS POTENTIAL 
-Behavior around children is unknown
-Potty trained

Lucy came to us from a shelter. She arrived at the shelter dog friendly and very kind. However, as the days went by and she kept getting overlooked, her behavior around dogs became uneasy. We welcomed her into our family with hopes of getting her back to the way she was before.

She is a HUGE cuddle bug who absolutely LOVES her humans! It will take her some time to get comfortable, but once she realizes you have nothing but love to give, she becomes the BEST companion ever! She enjoys napping to her people, watching TV and lounging outside. She is also a very smart pup who knows basic commands such as sit, down and stay!

Her foster family definitely has made her confidence go up, but she still needs work around pets. Because of this, Lucy will need someone who has NO pets in the home and/or someone who is willing to work through her trauma.

Lucy is only missing a little love in her life. We are sure that with the right family and dedication, Lucy will grow to love other dogs again!

She will do best in:
-A FENCED IN HOME!! 
-A home with NO pets
-Someone willing to TRAIN
-Someone ready to cuddle ALL DAY!

**A note from her foster: "Lucy is very loving. She may need time to trust at first. Once she knows you love her she will open up and thrive.
I believe Lucy will overcome any issues with lots of love."

!!DO NOT APPLY IF YOU LIVE IN AN APARTMENT!!
!!DO NOT APPLY IF YOU ARE NOT WILLING TO TRAIN!!
!!DO NOT APPLY IF YOU HAVE CATS!!

--YOUR APPLICATION WILL NOT BE CONSIDERED IF YOU LIVE IN AN APARTMENT OR HAVE CATS--

If you believe LUCY could be your pawwwfect match please fill out an adoption application: https://form.jotform.com/93263081961156

IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS PLEASE EMAIL INFO@MERCYFULLPROJECTS.ORG

animal.description:
It's galloping Gulliver! This guy is a real leggy goofball, a noodly wiggly dork. Gulliver is just bursting with excitement to get out on walks each day, and regularly entertains with his bouncy exuberance. He also has a curious and playful streak, and from the way his whole butt wiggles when he's greeting friends, an obviously big heart. A lot of his energy seems to be from feeing off the busy atmosphere at the kennel - we suspect that once he gets to unwind and settle into a routine in a home, he'll also budget plenty of time for folding his twiggy self up on the couch for some cuddles. Earnest Gulliver is around 2.5 years old and weighs around 50 lbs.

Visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to set up a meet!
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

12/17/20:
Hello everyone

My name is Sugar and this is my sister Oakley. We have been with Carolina Boxer Rescue a few weeks now and ready to find our forever home. My foster mom says that she is sure we will find a home that loves us just as much as she does. You see we come as a pair and she says its great because you get twice the love. Before coming into the rescue we had a very loving family, but sadly they couldn't keep us anymore so they did what they thought was best and reached out to the rescue. We are sure glad they did because we are getting super spoiled here with out foster parents.

They have a huge basket of toys here that we can play with when ever we feel like it. Sometimes we sneak them outside and play chase with them. We both love to run and play outside. I am a little quicker than my sister but I make sure to slow down so she can stay by my side. I would have to say my favorite toys are the ones with the squeakers but my sister Oakley loves nylon bones. You see, she can not hear the toys because the vet says she is almost deaf. Don't feel sorry for her though. She can be just as feisty as me. We both love car rides and like to see where we are going. If we see the leashes come out it is game one and the crazy excitement of out wiggle butts happen.

When it is down time just know I love to snuggle and they say I have no concept of personal space. I want to make sure you know I am right there by your side. As for my sister she is happy just laying at the foot of the bed or in her own dog bed. During the day since it has been so cold we been laying around in front of the fireplace and I have to say it feels great. Don't get me wrong we love to be outside but if we had a choice, in front of the fireplace it would be.

Well I am going to go now. I think I hear them calling my name for a treat.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting me or any of my friends here at the Brown County Humane Society, please call our voice mail number at 507-359-2312.  The shelter is open for adoptions on Saturdays from 11:00 a.m. to 2:00 p.m., so you can meet us. If Saturdays do not work, please call us so we can set up an appointment time to meet with you.

An Application to Adopt MUST be filled out prior to any adoptions. The application can be found on our website https://bchsnu.com/adoptions/ (scroll to the bottom of the page to find Adoption Forms) or by picking one up from the shelter.

All dogs have been vet checked, tested for heartworm, given age appropriate vaccinations, dewormed and spayed or neutered, if old enough. Heartworm testing may not have been done on puppies that are adopted out before they are old enough to be tested. Dog Adoption Fees are $125 (+MN State Sales Tax) for SPAYED or NEUTERED dogs/puppies OR $125 + $50 Deposit (+MN State Sales Tax) for dogs/puppies that have NOT YET BEEN SPAYED or NEUTERED. The $50 Deposit is refundable upon return of signed voucher from your Vet, by the date agreed upon with the adoption specialist. Senior dog (7 years or older) Adoption Fees are $55 (+MN State Sales Tax).

12/21/20:
Sally has been with us for a couple of weeks, and is a joy to foster! She's a spunky gal who loves to snuggle and give kisses, but also loves to play. Stuffed toys are her favorite, with nylabones and antlers a close second. She is good in the crate, but can also be left out if you put away her temptations- anything food related (like the garbage can) and writing implements (she just thinks they're for her!). She has learned how to go out the doggie door here, but prefers to be inside with her people. She loves to go for car rides and walks, but she is still working on her leash skills. She gets a little spooked by noises and new things on walks, so we are working on desensitizing her and helping her realize she's safe and it's okay. Our home is very quiet and she does great- we think she would do better with older children because she gets a little wild at times and doesn't realize how big she is. She also takes a bit of time to warm up to new people so needs a patient family who can give her that time. She will be spayed the beginning of January, and then will be ready for her forever home!

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Kiera is Shepherd mix (best guess) that was rescued from a high kill shelter in San Bernadino CA. She is estimated to be around 1 year old and joined us on December 13th. Our volunteer transporter reports that she is timid at first and will benefit from decompression time.

Foster Update: Kiera is settling in well, definitely timid initially and takes her a bit to warm up but then is very sweet and playful. She is pretty good with other dogs and has done well walking with other dogs for intros and passing them. She has shown some signs of resource guarding towards other dogs so we are looking at placing her in a home without other dogs. Kiera does ok in her crate, she's doing a lot better when switching up the routine when leaving.

Kiera would do well in a home without small children, someone who has some patience to give her time to warm up and work with her on her confidence. We also think she would make for an excellent agility companion given her willingness to jump on any playground equipment.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue. Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

Gender: Female

Dog's Weight: 41 pounds

Good with small dogs?: Don't know yet

Good with big dogs?: Yes

12/30/20: Hi, I'm Rose. I hope this doesn't take me too long to write because I have lots of playing to get to. So my FM says I have to write a little about myself and she told me I have to mention my size and energy. My FM calls me a "trial size" boxer. So I'm small, big deal. I really like this place I'm staying. There are three other dogs and kids to play with me and I love to PLAY. I love balls and ropes and sticks I find in the yard. I can make a toy of anything. My foster family says I play with intensity and purpose. I don't know why you'd do it any other way than that! I have gotten used to the routine around here and even appreciate when its time to get in the crate. I can't play hard if I don't rest hard. My foster family also seems to think its great that I don't bark at the people and dogs walking down the street like my foster brothers and sister. I don't know why I'd bark at them if I want them to play with me. They may like the way I act in the backyard, but they say I need to work on walking on leash. I don't understand why they won't just walk faster. I think this is their problem that they can't keep up with me. I am really good with kids but I can get overly excited if a human doesn't call me off. I do listen to commands, but I need reminding when I get excited. I am not food aggressive but I will eat out of the other bowls if the other dogs don't eat fast enough. I'd really like a forever home that has a playmate (or two) for me and a fenced backyard. House trained?: Yes

Heartworms?: No

12/19/20: Olaf has settled in well, he is a very easy going boy who loves to follow you around and get plenty of attention. He is great with our children who are 6 & 11. He has now been introduced to our resident boxers (female 7 & male 3), although you can tell he hasn't been socialized much with other dogs because he is very submissive and isn't quite sure how to be a dog and play. He is learning and just yesterday started to run around playing with my two and joined in with tossing a tennis ball around so he is definitely getting more comfortable with it.

Olaf is fully house trained and crate trained, the only continued training he needs is consistent work on his manners. animal.description:
SPECIAL NEEDS boy ... this amazing little guy is Wimble. He has overcome a lot and is a sweet, friendly dog who needs a special home to be loved forever. As of 1/1/21, Wimble is 20 weeks old (5 months) and approximately 21 lbs. He has limited vision in both eyes, but he gets around his foster home just fine and will adjust to your new home too in time, and with a slow acclimation process.

Wimble was found in a parking lot, completely malnourished and with a likely traumatic, brain injury. His finders didn't think he would survive that first night, and the next couple of nights either, but with lots of TLC, proper vet and medical care, he did. Today, he is an energetic, love bug who loves people, other dogs, cats and playing! 

Wimble is affectionate and friendly. He is working on crate training and house training, but slow and steady wins the race! He hasn't started leash training yet, but he has a big yard to play in right now with other dogs, so walking in the neighborhood isn't a high priority! 

Wimble loves to play with other dogs and his toys. He enjoys balls, ropes and stuffed toys. He also likes to snuggle with his humans. He will do best in a home when a human is home with him a fair amount of time. As he ages and continues to learn more about training, he will improve and do better being left alone for errands, etc. 

Don't pass up this great dog due to his disability. Give him a chance to thrive and blossom. He will likely be the best dog you have ever owned.

If you are interested in this dog, please contact volunteer Amy at amyh@rescuednready.com or at 918-688-0755.

ADOPTIONS ONLY TO PEOPLE LIVING IN THE NORTHEASTERN OKLAHOMA AREA.  

The adoption fee is $200.00 and includes all current vaccinations, negative heartworm test, worming, microchip, and spay/neuter surgery.  Go to www.rescuednready.com to learn about our adoption process and download our application.  

CALL or EMAIL US TO MEET ONE OF OUR ADOPTABLE DOGS! Call Amy at 918-688-0755 or email at amyh@rescuednready.com.

LIKE RESCUED 'N READY ON FACEBOOK!!

He’s house trained, and crate trained (loves his crate).  He’s learning a lot in his foster home, such as realizing that not all humans are bad, and that he likes other dogs and cats. He’s picking up on commands quickly.  
Pedro should not be in a home with young children, as they scare him.  
Pedro is ready for his furever family!

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

12/30/20: Hi all,

My name is Pluto and I have been searching for love in all the wrong places. I am a 3 years young, super handsome, playful and loving if you ask me!

My ideal match would be people who will make me their one and only. I am not crazy about sharing my love with other furry ones.

I have learned some great tricks like sitting on command and I am a great listener. I would love to show you what a gentleman I am learning to become!

I do need the luxury of a dog door and a six foot fence. My kidneys are not fully functional, but that doesn't hold me back from being active and my vet professional says I can have many years of love to share. I just have a special type of food I require and check ups with my doctor occasionally.

So really that's about it. I give you tons of love, snuggles and my silly playful self in exchange for a warm bed, my special food and a dog door with a fenced yard.

Oh and I really love to go on long walks and rides in the car too. Maybe even a trip to Lowes? If you want to get a little wild one day.

animal.special_needs_notes: When Kimmie came to us in August she little to no use of her back legs. She was also incontinent. Through Steroid therapy and acupuncture once a week for several months, Kimmie is able to use her back legs to walk and has regained some bladder and bowel control.  She still has accidents, but has greatly improved since we have started taking her outside every 2-3 hours.  This was due to a back injury. No rough play climbing jumping.  Getting acupuncture every 3 weeks. Our goal is once a month. She has some separation anxiety when you first leave.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.**** Located in Tampa, FL - Needs another dog in the home and a fully fenced yard. ****

Nessa has a sad story - she was found as a 4 month old puppy, locked in a hotel closet with a broken front elbow. Whoever put her there did not care about her at all. She was scared, confused and unsure how to trust. Second Chance answered her rescue plea from the shelter. Nessa had surgery to repair her elbow by one of the best in Tampa and she has fully healed up.

Her emotional scars are still there. She is not fond of children and the sound of kids makes her uncomfortable.

She likes to chase/play with the cats in her foster home and has made lots of doggie friends there too - so much so,
Nessa will need another dog in her forever home.

Being on crate rest for months has limited her exposure but we are working on that. She enjoys walks in the neighborhood, playing with toys and running in the back yard so a fenced yard is a on her wish list.

Nessa also likes to cuddle on the couch and watch a good movie. We are looking for the very best home for her that will give her the love she deserves. Nessa is 7 months old and 35lbs.

Available Tampa, FL - Adoption fee is $250.00

Fully vetted, chipped, HW Negative and spayed. Fenced Yard a must.

He loves to play ball and runs and jumps like a pup.  He would love an active friend to help him stay fit and looking great!  Sam was in a home with adults and children and loves everyone (NOT CATS THOUGH). As Shepherds do, he will bark when there is a knock at the door or at visitors outside.

Out of state dog adoptions $300

TOUCH a SOUL.  CHANGE a LIFE.  PERHAPS your OWN.

FREE spay/neuter email adopt@thisisthedog.org


This is the Dog! (TITD!) makes no representation, warranty or guarantee about an animal’s breed, temperament or behavior. animal.description:
Meet Mateo and Mila! These bonded Sweeties are 1.5 years and 65 lbs. They are Potty trained And Not destructive at the foster home. They love to chew toys! They are Obsessed with bones and toys, especially squeaky ones! They still have puppy play behavior, which is cute!

They love to play with each other which can sometimes be kind of rough play but its nothing abnormal. They were found together hovered over each other in a ditch, so they are bonded and they are there for each other. Theyve grown a lot with confidence and they continue to grow. 

Mateo and Mila can be kind of hyper when you first get home and bring them in because theyre excited to see you, but in about 15 minutes they settle and lay down and cuddle. 

They come up to you for love, it is precious. they want you to hold them! They love to be next to their person. 

They do not know any tricks but could certainly be taught! 

They get nervous at first when new people come over to the foster home. The foster dad has visitors give a treat then the dogs seem to calm down and feel normal around the new person after a few minutes. 

They have not shown any aggression towards other dogs while in our care. 

Mateo is more confident meeting other dogs and people. Mila is very submissive. 

The worst they do is bark in the yard when someone comes up to the fence. This is the only time they bark at the foster home. 

The cutest thing is the way they love each other. They cuddle together like a cinnamon roll! 

On leash they need a little work with pulling and recall. 

In the car theyre curious looking out the window or they just lay down. 

These are precious rescued dogs! They deserve the best! 

Email Alayna@threelittlepittiesrescue.org with questions but best thing to do is to go ahead and fill out an application.

The adoption fee is $650 for the bonded pair. He/she is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee!

He/she may currently be fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW as soon as he/she finds her perfect home or may be traveling to a foster in the PNW soon. 

Due to the Covid-19 crisis we are experiencing a dramatic influx in inquiries and adoption applications. If you have questions regarding a pup you are interested in please fill out an adoption application. Once received it can take up to a week to complete our review. Be assured we have received your received your application! If you need more information regarding a pup you are interested in, the process of filling out an adoption application is still required prior to answering detailed questions. We value our potential adopters time and appreciate your patience as our staff navigate through the blessing of an overwhelming response for adoptions.

Please inquire by submitting an application to Alayna@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/19753/generic

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

She will need a home with a backyard where she can do her zoomies and get some exercise! This sweet gal has a lot of puppy in her so we are working on some house manners and some basic commands. She’s incredibly smart and she's learning all of her sign commands. Evangelina likes all the belly rubs and scratches she can possibly get from her people! She will be fully vetted, vaccinated and microchipped prior to adoption.

We will require Evangelina to be in training within 10 days of adoption. Basic obedience training is crucial  for young pups like Evangelina to mature and grow into wonderful companions! It’s also a great opportunity for Evangelina and her new family to bond with each other.

For more information about our adoption process and an application please visit www.whitekissesgreatdanerescue.com/adopt

animal.description:
Hi my name is Gnocchi! I’m 2 years old and 45-50 lbs! I was found with my four puppies in an abandoned trailer.  Luckily, ODHS rescued me and they have taken care of me ever since. My foster family has taken me from a skinny gal, to one that looks super healthy.

Here are some things to know about me:
1. I love my humans and getting pets, snuggles,  and attention.
2. I take treats like a lady and I am very gentle overall.
3. Good about telling my family when I need to go outside for potty time.
4. Learned the command "sit"

Things I am working on:
1. Being crated (I don't like it so far and this is probably because I have never been crated before).
2. Learning to be a "dog" after being neglected at an early age.

You can come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational articles:
3/3/3 Rule;
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturdays. 
Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.

********If dog/pup is showing as available it is available. Please do not email asking if it is. Submit application to meet dog if interested - yes an application is required********

REQUIREMENTS: live in the Rochester NY area (within 1/2 drive) and have a physically fenced in yard for pup to safely run and play in.

Meet Tara: This beautiful pup was born Nov 5th/2020.  DNA came back with 14 breeds in her so she is a super mutt. Expect her to be around 50 to 60 lbs as an adult.   If you're looking for a puppy to go with you on adventures, Tara is your girl.  She loves new smells, new places, and meeting new people. She is very bright pup and is almost house-trained plus knows some basic commands.  She is working on good walking right now too. She has a mind of her own and a great personality! Her lifestyle is to play hard and sleep hard (preferably on your lap).
She will be spayed and 2nd round of vaccines on Feb 2nd. If you would like to meet this adorable pup an application must be filled out https://www.cognitoforms.com/New2URescues/AdoptionApplication

You can learn more about our rescue and process at www.new2urescue.org or find us on facebook at https://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ must be filled out to meet one of our dogs.  You must be 25 yrs of age or older to adopt through us. We are in the Rochester NY area and adopt dogs out to area residents.


https://www.cognitoforms.com/New2URescues/AdoptionApplication
An application must be filled out to meet any of our dogs, to apply go to 
http://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ so foster can contact you. We do not have a shelter, dogs are in foster homes.

All animals are kept in foster homes so there is no shelter for you to visit animal. Please go to https://new2urescue.org/adoption/adoption-application/ if you would like to meet the foster animal or learn more.

All our dogs have been spayed/neutered; treated for worms; heartworm tested (if age appropriate -7 mths or older); treated for fleas/ticks; microchip; and examined by veterinarian and given age appropriate vaccinations. We take every effort to ensure the health of the animal and you will receive a copy of all vet work performed.

You can find us on Face Book at https://www.facebook.com/New2Urescue and our main website at https://www.new2urescue.org

New 2 U Rescue is registered as a New York State Shelter / Rescue. Our Registration No.: is RR033 and we are a Registered Non Profit with a 501c3. We help dogs in need in the Greater Rochester, NY area by taking them in, providing any needed vet care and helping them find a forever home.
